#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The rules directory must be located in the same directory specified via the "
"<literal>autoyast</literal> keyword at boot time. If the client was booted "
"using <literal>autoyast=http://10.10.0.1/profiles/</literal> , &ay; will "
"search for the rules file at http://10.10.0.1/profiles/rules/rules.xml."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15360
#, no-c-format
msgid "Custom Rules"
msgstr "独自のルール"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15361
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If the attributes &ay; provides for rules are not enough for your purposes, "
"use custom rules. Custom rules contain a shell script. The output of the "
"script (STDOUT, STDERR is ignored) can be evaluated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15366
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is an example for the use of custom rules:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;rule&gt;\n"
"  &lt;custom1&gt;\n"
"    &lt;script&gt;\n"
"if grep -i intel /proc/cpuinfo &gt; /dev/null; then\n"
"echo -n \"intel\"\n"
"else\n"
"echo -n \"non_intel\"\n"
"fi;\n"
"    &lt;/script&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match&gt;*&lt;/match&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match_type&gt;exact&lt;/match_type&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/custom1&gt;\n"
"  &lt;result&gt;\n"
"    &lt;profile&gt;@custom1@.xml&lt;/profile&gt;\n"
"    &lt;continue config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/continue&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/result&gt;\n"
"&lt;/rule&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The script in this rule can echo either <literal>intel</literal> or "
"<literal>non_intel</literal> to STDOUT (the output of the grep command must "
"be directed to /dev/null in this case). The output of the rule script will "
"be filled between the two '@' characters, to determine the file name of the "
"control file to fetch. &ay; will read the output and fetch a file with the "
"name <filename>intel.xml</filename> or <filename>non_intel.xml</filename> . "
"This file can contain the &ay; profile part for the software selection; for "
"example, in case you want a different software selection on Intel hardware "
"than on others."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The number of custom rules is limited to five. So you can use "
"<literal>custom1</literal> to <literal>custom5</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15404
#, no-c-format
msgid "Match Types for Rules"
msgstr "ルールで使用する比較種類"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15405
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can use five different match_types:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15410
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>exact</literal> (default)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15415
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>greater</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15420
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>lower</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15425
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>range</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15430
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>regex</literal> (a simple <literal>=~</literal> operator like in "
"Bash)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15436
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If using <literal>exact</literal> , the string must match exactly as "
"specified. <literal>regex</literal> can be used to match substrings like "
"<literal>ntel</literal> will match Intel, intel and intelligent. "
"<literal>greater</literal> and <literal>lower</literal> can be used for "
"<literal>memsize</literal> or <literal>totaldisk</literal> for example. They "
"can match only with rules that return an integer value. A range is only "
"possible for integer values too and has the form of <literal>value1-value2</"
"literal> , for example <literal>512-1024</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15449
#, no-c-format
msgid "Combine Attributes"
msgstr "属性の組み合わせ"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15450
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Multiple attributes can be combined via a logical operator. It is possible "
"to let a rule match if <literal>disksize</literal> is greater than 1GB or "
"<literal>memsize</literal> is exactly 512MB."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15455
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can do this with the <literal>operator</literal> element in the rules."
"xml file. <literal>and</literal> and <literal>or</literal> are possible "
"operators, <literal>and</literal> being the default. Here is an example:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:15461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;rule&gt;\n"
"  &lt;disksize&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match&gt;/dev/sda 1000&lt;/match&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match_type&gt;greater&lt;/match_type&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/disksize&gt;\n"
"  &lt;memsize&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match&gt;256&lt;/match&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match_type&gt;greater&lt;/match_type&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/memsize&gt;\n"
"  &lt;result&gt;\n"
"    &lt;profile&gt;machine2.xml&lt;/profile&gt;\n"
"    &lt;continue config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/continue&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/result&gt;\n"
"  &lt;operator&gt;or&lt;/operator&gt;\n"
"&lt;/rule&gt;"
msgstr ""

