"      &lt;continue config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/continue&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/result&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/rule&gt;\n"
"&lt;/rules&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16147
#, no-c-format
msgid "Classes"
msgstr "クラス"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Classes represent configurations for groups of target systems. Unlike rules, "
"classes need to be configured in the control file. Then classes can be "
"assigned to target systems."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Here is an example of a class definition:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16159
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;classes config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;class&gt;\n"
"    &lt;class_name&gt;TrainingRoom&lt;/class_name&gt;\n"
"    &lt;configuration&gt;Software.xml&lt;/configuration&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/class&gt;\n"
"&lt;/classes&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16166
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the example above, the file <filename>Software.xml</filename> must be "
"placed in the subdirectory <filename>classes/TrainingRoom/</filename> It "
"will be fetched from the same place the &ay; control file and rules were "
"fetched from."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have multiple control files and those control files share parts, "
"better use classes for common parts. <!--You just need to change the class "
"and all profiles using that class are fixed too.--> <remark>emap 2011-11-07: "
"Sentence does not make sense.</remark> You can also use XIncludes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the configuration management system, you can define a set of classes. "
"A class definition consists of the following variables:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Name: class name"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16193
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Order: order (or priority) of the class in the stack of migration "
"<remark>emap 2011-11-07: What migration?</remark>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining Classes"
msgstr "クラスの定義"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can create as many classes as you need, however it is recommended to "
"keep the set of classes as small as possible to keep the configuration "
"system concise. For example, the following sets of classes can be used:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16237
#, no-c-format
msgid "site: classes describing a physical location or site,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16242
#, no-c-format
msgid "machine: classes describing a type of machine,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16247
#, no-c-format
msgid "role: classes describing the function of the machine,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16252
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"group: classes describing a department or a group within a site or a "
"location."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16259
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A file saved in a class directory can have the same syntax and format as a "
"regular control file but represents a subset of the configuration. For "
"example, to create a new control file for a computer with a specific network "
"interface, you only need the control file resource that controls the "
"configuration of the network. Having multiple network types, you can merge "
"the one needed for a special type of hardware with other class files and "
"create a new control file which suits the system being installed. "
"<remark>emap 2011-11-07: Not very clear.</remark>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16272
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mixing Rules and Classes"
msgstr "ルールとクラスの混合"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16274
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"It is possible to mix rules and classes during an auto-installation session. "
"For example you can identify a system using rules which contain class "
"definitions in them. The process is described in the figure <xref linkend="
"\"rulesflow\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16281
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After retrieving the rules and merging them, the generated control file is "
"parsed and checked for class definitions. If classes are defined, then the "
"class files are retrieved from the original repository and a new merge "
"process is initiated."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16289
#, no-c-format
msgid "Merging of Rules and Classes"
msgstr "ルールとクラスの合成"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16291
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With classes and with rules, multiple XML files get merged into one "
"resulting XML file. This merging process is often confusing for people, "
"because it behaves different than one would expect. First of all, it is "
"important to note that the names of the top sections in the merged XML files "
"must be in alphabetical order for the merge to succeed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16299
#, no-c-format
msgid "For example, the following two XML parts should be merged:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16303
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;partitioning config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;drive&gt;\n"
"    &lt;partitions config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;partition&gt;\n"
"        &lt;filesystem config:type=\"symbol\"&gt;swap&lt;/filesystem&gt;\n"
"        &lt;format config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/format&gt;\n"
"        &lt;mount&gt;swap&lt;/mount&gt;\n"
"        &lt;partition_id config:type=\"integer\"&gt;130&lt;/"
"partition_id&gt;\n"
"        &lt;size&gt;2000mb&lt;/size&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/partition&gt;\n"
"      &lt;partition&gt;\n"
"        &lt;filesystem config:type=\"symbol\"&gt;xfs&lt;/filesystem&gt;\n"
"        &lt;partition_type&gt;primary&lt;/partition_type&gt;\n"
"        &lt;size&gt;4Gb&lt;/size&gt;\n"
"        &lt;mount&gt;/data&lt;/mount&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/partition&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/partitions&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/drive&gt;\n"
"&lt;/partitioning&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16323
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;partitioning config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;drive&gt;\n"
"    &lt;initialize config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/initialize&gt;\n"
"    &lt;partitions config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;partition&gt;\n"
"        &lt;format config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/format&gt;\n"
"        &lt;filesystem config:type=\"symbol\"&gt;xfs&lt;/filesystem&gt;\n"
"        &lt;mount&gt;/&lt;/mount&gt;\n"
"        &lt;partition_id config:type=\"integer\"&gt;131&lt;/"
"partition_id&gt;\n"
"        &lt;partition_type&gt;primary&lt;/partition_type&gt;\n"
"        &lt;size&gt;max&lt;/size&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/partition&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/partitions&gt;\n"
"    &lt;use&gt;all&lt;/use&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/drive&gt;\n"
"&lt;/partitioning&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You might expect the control file to contain three partitions. This is not "
"the case. You will end up with two partitions and the first partition is a "
"mix up of the swap and the root partition. Settings configured in both "
"partitions, like <literal>mount</literal> or <literal>size</literal> , will "
"be used from the second file. Settings that only exist in the first or "
"second partition, will be copied to the merged partition too. <remark>emap "
"2011-11-07: A little confusing, why not put the merged file here.</remark>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16350
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this example, you do not want a second <literal>drive</literal> . The two "
"drives should be merged into one. With regard to partitions, three separate "
"ones should be defined. Using the <literal>dont_merge</literal> method "
"solves the merging problem:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;classes config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;class&gt;\n"
"    &lt;class_name&gt;swap&lt;/class_name&gt;\n"
"    &lt;configuration&gt;largeswap.xml&lt;/configuration&gt;\n"
"    &lt;dont_merge config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;element&gt;partition&lt;/element&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/dont_merge&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/class&gt;\n"
"&lt;/classes&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16367
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;rule&gt;\n"
"  &lt;board_vendor&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match&gt;ntel&lt;/match&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match_type&gt;regex&lt;/match_type&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/board_vendor&gt;\n"
"  &lt;result&gt;\n"
"    &lt;profile&gt;classes/largeswap.xml&lt;/profile&gt;\n"
"    &lt;continue config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/continue&gt;\n"
"    &lt;dont_merge config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;element&gt;partition&lt;/element&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/dont_merge&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/result&gt;\n"
"  &lt;board_vendor&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match&gt;PowerEdge [12]850&lt;/match&gt;\n"
"    &lt;match_type&gt;regex&lt;/match_type&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/board_vendor&gt;\n"
"  &lt;result&gt;\n"
"    &lt;profile&gt;classes/smallswap.xml&lt;/profile&gt;\n"
"    &lt;continue config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/continue&gt;\n"
"    &lt;dont_merge config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;element&gt;partition&lt;/element&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/dont_merge&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/result&gt;\n"
"&lt;/rule&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16394
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Auto-Installation Process"
msgstr "自動インストール処理"

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16398
#, no-c-format
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "紹介"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16400
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"After the system has booted into an automatic installation and the control "
"file has been retrieved, &yast; configures the system according to the "
"information provided in the control file. All configuration settings are "
"summarized in a window that is shown by default and should be deactivated if "
"a fully automatic installation is needed."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16409
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By the time &yast; displays the summary of the configuration, &yast; has "
"only probed hardware and prepared the system for auto-installation. Nothing "
"has been changed in the system yet. In case of any error, you can still "
"abort the process."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16416
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A system should be automatically installable without the need to have any "
"graphic adapter or monitor. Having a monitor attached to the client machine "
"is nevertheless recommended so you can supervise the process and to get "
"feedback in case of errors. Choose between the graphical and the text-based "
"Ncurses interfaces. For headless clients, system messages can be monitored "
"using the serial console."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16426
#, no-c-format
msgid "X11 Interface (graphical)"
msgstr "X11 インターフェイス (グラフィカル)"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the default interface while auto-installing. No special variables "
"are required to activate it."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16434
#, no-c-format
msgid "Serial Console"
msgstr "シリアルコンソール"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16435
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Start installing a system using the serial console by adding the keyword "
"<literal>console</literal> (for example <literal>console=ttyS0</literal> ) "
"to the command line of the kernel. This starts <command>linuxrc</command> in "
"console mode and later &yast; in serial console mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16445
#, no-c-format
msgid "Text-based &yast; Installation"
msgstr "テキストベースの &yast; インストール"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16446
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option can also be activated on the command line. To start &yast; in "
"text mode, add <literal>textmode=1</literal> on the command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16451
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Starting &yast; in the text mode is recommended when installing a client "
"with less than 64 MB or when X11 should not be configured, especially on "
"headless machines."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16459
#, no-c-format
msgid "Choosing the Right Boot Medium"
msgstr "適切な起動メディアの選択"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16461
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are different methods for booting the client. The computer can boot "
"from its network interface card (NIC) to receive the boot images via DHCP or "
"TFTP. Alternatively a suitable kernel and initrd image can be loaded from a "
"flash disk or a bootable DVD-ROM."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&yast; will check for <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> in the root "
"directory of the boot medium or the initrd upon start-up and switch to an "
"automated installation if it was found. In case the control file is named "
"differently or located elsewhere, specify its location on the kernel command "
"line with the parameter <literal>&ay;=<replaceable>URL</replaceable></"
"literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16478
#, no-c-format
msgid "Booting from a Flash Disk"
msgstr "フラッシュメモリからの起動"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16479
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For testing/rescue purposes or because the NIC does not have a PROM or PXE "
"you can build a bootable flash disk to use with &ay;. Flash disks can also "
"store the control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16485
#, no-c-format
msgid "Creating a Bootable Flash Disk"
msgstr "起動可能なフラッシュメモリの作成"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16486
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To create a bootable flash disk, copy either the &productname; ISO image of "
"DVD1 or the Mini CD ISO image to the disk using the <command>dd</command> "
"command (the flash disk must not be mounted, all data on the device will be "
"erased):"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16492
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;dd if=PATH_TO_ISO_IMAGE of=USB_STORAGE_DEVICE bs=4M"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16497
#, no-c-format
msgid "Booting from DVD-ROM"
msgstr "DVD-ROM からの起動"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16498
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use the original &productname; DVD-ROM number one in combination "
"with other media. For example, the control file can be provided via a flash "
"disk or a specified location on the network. Alternatively, create a "
"customized DVD-ROM that includes the control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16508
#, no-c-format
msgid "Booting via PXE over the Network"
msgstr "ネットワーク経由での PXE 起動"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16509
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Booting via PXE requires a DHCP and a TFTP server in your network. The "
"computer will then boot without a physical medium. <phrase os=\"sles;sled"
"\">For instructions on setting up the required infrastructure, see <xref "
"linkend=\"cha.remote_installation\"/>.</phrase>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16515
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you install via PXE, the installation will run in an endless loop. This "
"happens because after the first reboot, the machine performs the PXE boot "
"again and restarts the installation instead of booting from the hard disk "
"for the second stage of the installation."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16521
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are several ways to solve this problem. You can use an HTTP server to "
"provide the &ay; control file. Alternatively, instead of a static control "
"file, run a CGI script on the Web server that provides the control file and "
"changes the TFTP server configuration for your target host. This way, the "
"next PXE boot of the machine will be from the hard disk by default."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16529
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another way is to use &ay; to upload a new PXE boot configuration for the "
"target host via the control file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16533
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;pxe&gt;\n"
"  &lt;pxe_localboot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/pxe_localboot&gt;\n"
"  &lt;pxelinux-config&gt;\n"
"    DEFAULT linux\n"
"    LABEL linux\n"
"    localboot 0\n"
"  &lt;/pxelinux-config&gt;\n"
"  &lt;tftp-server&gt;&tftpip;&lt;/tftp-server&gt;\n"
"  &lt;pxelinux-dir&gt;/pxelinux.cfg&lt;/pxelinux-dir&gt;\n"
"  &lt;filename&gt;__MAC__&lt;/filename&gt;\n"
"&lt;/pxe&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16544
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This entry will upload a new configuration for the target host to the TFTP "
"server shortly before the first reboot happens. In most installations the "
"TFTP daemon runs as user <systemitem class=\"username\">nobody</"
"systemitem> . You need to make sure this user has write permissions to the "
"<filename>pxelinux.cfg</filename> directory. You can also configure the file "
"name that will be uploaded. If you use the <quote>magic</quote> "
"<literal>__MAC__</literal> file name, the file name will be the MAC address "
"of your machine like, for example <literal>01-08-00-27-79-49-ee</literal> . "
"If the file name setting is missing, the IP address will be used for the "
"file name."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16557
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To do another auto-installation on the same machine, you need to remove the "
"file from the TFTP server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16564
#, no-c-format
msgid "Invoking the Auto-Installation Process"
msgstr "自動インストール処理の開始"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16566
#, no-c-format
msgid "<remark role=\"fixme\">Add a short description</remark>"
msgstr "<remark role=\"fixme\">Add a short description</remark>"

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16571
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line Options"
msgstr "コマンドラインオプション"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16572
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Adding the command line variable <literal>autoyast</literal> causes "
"<command>linuxrc</command> to start in automated mode. The <command>linuxrc</"
"command> program searches for a configuration file, which should be "
"distinguished from the main control file, in the following places:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16580
#, no-c-format
msgid "in the root directory of the initial RAM disk used for booting the system;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16586
#, no-c-format
msgid "in the root directory of the boot medium."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16591
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>linuxrc</command> configuration file supports multiple "
"keywords. For a detailed description of how <command>linuxrc</command> works "
"and other keywords, see <xref linkend=\"appendix.linuxrc\"/> . Some of the "
"more common ones are:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16598
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keywords for <command>linuxrc</command>"
msgstr "<command>linuxrc</command> のキーワード"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16603
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keyword"
msgstr "キーワード"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16608
#, no-c-format
msgid "Value"
msgstr "値"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16617
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoupgrade</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Initiate an automatic upgrade using &ay;; see <xref linkend=\"CreateProfile."
"upgrade\"/> . For some use cases, you need the <literal>autoyast</literal> "
"parameter (see <xref linkend=\"Commandline.ay\"/> for details)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16631
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Location of the control file for automatic installation; see <xref linkend="
"\"Commandline.ay\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16644
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast2</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16649
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Location of the control file for automatic installation. Similar to the "
"<literal>autoyast</literal> option, but <command>linuxrc</command> parses "
"the provided value and, for example, tries to configure a network when "
"needed. For information about differences between the &ay; and "
"<command>linuxrc</command> URI syntax, see the <command>linuxrc</command> "
"appendix: <xref linkend=\"appendix.linuxrc\"/> . &ay;'s rules and classes "
"are <emphasis>not</emphasis> supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16663
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>ifcfg</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16668
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Configure and start the network. Required if the &ay; is to be fetched from "
"a remote location. See <xref linkend=\"ay.adv_network\"/> for details."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16704
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>insmod</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16709
#, no-c-format
msgid "Kernel modules to load"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16716
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>install</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16721
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Location of the installation directory, for example "
"<literal>install=nfs://192.168.2.1/CDs/</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16729
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>instmode</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16734
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Installation mode, for example <literal>nfs</literal> , <literal>http</"
"literal> etc. (not needed if <literal>install</literal> is set)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16782
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>rootpassword</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16787
#, no-c-format
msgid "Password for root user if not specified in &ay; profile"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16794
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>server</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16799
#, no-c-format
msgid "Server (NFS) to contact for source directory"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16806
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>serverdir</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16811
#, no-c-format
msgid "Directory on NFS Server"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16823
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Even with &lt;confirm&gt;no&lt;/confirm&gt; in the control file, the confirm "
"proposal comes up."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16832
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These variables and keywords will bring the system up to the point where "
"&yast; can take over with the main control file. Currently, the source "
"medium is automatically discovered, which in some cases makes it possible to "
"initiate the auto-install process without giving any instructions to "
"<command>linuxrc</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16839
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The traditional <command>linuxrc</command> configuration file "
"( <filename>info</filename> ) has the function of giving the client enough "
"information about the installation server and the location of the sources. "
"Usually, this file is not required, but it is needed in special network "
"environments where DHCP and BOOTP are not used or when special kernel "
"modules need to be loaded."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16847
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can pass keywords to <command>linuxrc</command> using the kernel command "
"line. This can be done in several ways. You can specify <command>linurc</"
"command> keywords along with other kernel parameters interactively at boot "
"time, in the usual way. You can also insert kernel parameters into custom "
"network-bootable disk images. It is also possible to configure a DHCP server "
"to pass kernel parameters in combination with Etherboot or PXE."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16856
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The command line variable <literal>autoyast</literal> can be used in the "
"format described in table <xref linkend=\"Commandline.ay\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16861
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command Line Variables for &ay;"
msgstr "&ay; 向けのコマンドライン変数"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16866
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command line variable"
msgstr "コマンドライン変数"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16880
#, no-c-format
msgid "missing"
msgstr "(無し)"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16885
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"No <literal>autoyast</literal> variable needed for an automated upgrade, see "
"<xref linkend=\"pro.upgrade.upgrade-mode\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16893
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=default</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16898
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default auto-installation option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16905
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=file:///<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16910
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Looks for control file in specified path (relative to the source root "
"directory, for example <literal>file:///autoinst.xml</literal> if in the top "
"directory of a CD-ROM and you did an installation from CD)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16920
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>autoyast=device://<replaceable>DEVICE</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16925
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Looks for control file on a storage device. Do not specify the full path to "
"the device, but the device name only. You may also omit specifying the "
"device and trigger &ay; to search all devices ( <literal>autoyast=device:///"
"<replaceable>FILENAME</replaceable></literal> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16935
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>autoyast=nfs://<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/<replaceable>PATH</"
"replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16940
#, no-c-format
msgid "Looks for control file on an NFS server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16947
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>autoyast=http://[user:password@]<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16952
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Retrieves the control file from a Web server using the HTTP protocol. "
"Specifying a user name and a password is optional."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16960
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>autoyast=https://[user:password@]<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16965
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Retrieves the control file from a Web server using HTTPS. Specifying a user "
"name and a password is optional."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16973
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>autoyast=tftp://<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16978
#, no-c-format
msgid "Retrieve the control file via TFTP."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16985
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>autoyast=ftp://[user:password@]<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16990
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Retrieve the control file via FTP. Specifying a user name and a password is "
"optional."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:16998
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=usb://<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17003
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Retrieve the control file from USB devices (&ay; will search all connected "
"USB devices)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17011
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=relurl://<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17016
#, no-c-format
msgid "Retrieve the control file from the installation source (install=....)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17024
#, no-c-format
msgid "<literal>autoyast=slp</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17029
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Query the location of the control file from an SLP server (service:"
"autoyast:...). Optionally you may add a <literal>description=</literal> "
"attribute so you can <quote>translate</quote> the URL into something more "
"readable. ( <literal>autoyast=slp:/?descr=*SLES*</literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17040
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>autoyast=cifs://<replaceable>SERVER</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17045
#, no-c-format
msgid "Looks for control file on a CIFS server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17052
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<literal>autoyast=label://<replaceable>LABEL</replaceable>/"
"<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></literal>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17057
#, no-c-format
msgid "Searches for a control file on a device with the specified label"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17065
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Several scenarios for auto-installation are possible using different types "
"of infrastructure and source media. The simplest way is to use the source "
"media (DVD number one) of &productname;. But to initiate the auto-"
"installation process, the auto-installation command-line variable should be "
"entered at system boot-up and the control file should be accessible for "
"&yast;."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17073
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In a scripting context, you can use a serial console for your virtual "
"machine, that allows you to work in text mode. Then you can pass the needed "
"parameters from an expect script or equivalent."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17076
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following list of scenarios explains how the control file can be "
"supplied:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17081
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using the Original &productname; DVD-ROM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17083
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using the original DVD-ROM (DVD #1 is needed), the control file needs "
"to be accessible via flash disk or network:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17110
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using a Custom DVD-ROM"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17112
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this case, you can include the control file directly on the DVD-ROM. When "
"placing it in the root directory and naming it <filename>autoinst.xml</"
"filename> , it will automatically be found and used for the installation. "
"Otherwise use <literal>autoyast=file:///<replaceable>PATH</replaceable></"
"literal> to specify the path to the control file."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using a DVD-ROM for auto-installation, it is necessary to instruct the "
"installer to use the DVD-ROM for installation instead of trying to find the "
"installation files on the network. This can be done by adding the "
"<literal>instmode=cd</literal> option to the kernel command line (this can "
"be automated by adding the option to the <filename>isolinux.cfg</filename> "
"file on the DVD)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using a Network Installation Source"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17133
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This option is the most important one because installations of multiple "
"machines are usually done using SLP or NFS servers and other network "
"services like BOOTP and DHCP. The easiest way to make the control file "
"available is to place it in the root directory of the installation source, "
"naming it <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> . In this case, it will "
"automatically be found and used for the installation. The control file can "
"also reside in the following places:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17143
#, no-c-format
msgid "Flash Disk"
msgstr "フラッシュメモリ"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17144
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Access the control file via the <literal>autoyast=usb://<replaceable>PATH</"
"replaceable></literal> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17151
#, no-c-format
msgid "Network"
msgstr "ネットワーク"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17152
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Access the control file via the following commands: "
"<literal>autoyast=nfs://..</literal> , <literal>autoyast=ftp://..</"
"literal> , <literal>autoyast=http://..</literal> , "
"<literal>autoyast=https://..</literal> , <literal>autoyast=tftp://..</"
"literal> , or <literal>autoyast=cifs://..</literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17166
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disabling Network and DHCP"
msgstr "ネットワークと DHCP の無効化について"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17167
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To disable the network during installations where it is not needed or "
"unavailable, for example when auto-installing from DVD-ROMs, use the "
"<command>linuxrc</command> option <literal>netsetup=0</literal> to disable "
"the network setup."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17175
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Difference between the <literal>autoyast</literal> and <literal>autoyast2</"
"literal> Options"
msgstr "<literal>autoyast</literal> と <literal>autoyast2</literal> のオプションの違いについて"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17179
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The options <literal>autoyast</literal> and <literal>autoyast2</literal> are "
"very similar but differ in one important point:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17185
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you use <literal>autoyast=http://...</literal> , you need to provide "
"<command>linuxrc</command> with the network configuration."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17191
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you use <literal>autoyast2=http://...</literal> , <command>linuxrc</"
"command> tries to configure the network for you."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17198
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If <literal>autoyast=default</literal> is defined, &yast; will look for a "
"file named <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> in the following three places:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17205
#, no-c-format
msgid "the root directory of the flash disk,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17210
#, no-c-format
msgid "the root directory of the installation medium,"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17215
#, no-c-format
msgid "the root directory of the initial RAM disk used to boot the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With all &ay; invocation options, excluding <literal>default</literal> , it "
"is possible to specify the location of the control file in the following "
"ways:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17228
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify the exact location of the control file:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17231
#, no-c-format
msgid "autoyast=http://192.168.1.1/control-files/client01.xml"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17234
#, no-c-format
msgid "Specify a directory where several control files are located:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17237
#, no-c-format
msgid "autoyast=http://192.168.1.1/control-files/"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17238
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this case the relevant control file is retrieved using the hex digit "
"representation of the IP as described below."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17244
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If only the path prefix variable is defined, &yast; will fetch the control "
"file from the specified location in the following way:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17251
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First, it will search for the control file using its own IP address in "
"uppercase hexadecimal, for example <literal>192.0.2.91 -&gt; C000025B</"
"literal> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17258
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this file is not found, &yast; will remove one hex digit and try again. "
"This action is repeated until the file with the correct name is found. "
"Ultimately, it will try looking for a file with the MAC address of the "
"client as the file name (mac should have the following syntax: "
"<literal>0080C8F6484C</literal> ) and if not found a file named "
"<filename>default</filename> (in lowercase)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17268
#, no-c-format
msgid "As an example, for 192.0.2.91, the HTTP client will try:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17272
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"C000025B\n"
"C000025\n"
"C00002\n"
"C0000\n"
"C000\n"
"C00\n"
"C0\n"
"C\n"
"0080C8F6484C\n"
"default"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17282
#, no-c-format
msgid "in that order."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17285
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To determine the hex representation of the IP address of the client, use the "
"utility called <command>/usr/bin/gethostip</command> available with the "
"<systemitem class=\"resource\">syslinux</systemitem> package."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17291
#, no-c-format
msgid "Determine HEX code for an IP address"
msgstr "IP アドレスの 16 進数表記への変換"

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17292
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&prompt.user;/usr/bin/gethostip 10.10.0.1\n"
"10.10.0.1 10.10.0.1 0A0A0001"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17298
#, no-c-format
msgid "Auto-installing a Single System"
msgstr "単一システムの自動インストール"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17299
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The easiest way to auto-install a system without any network connection is "
"to use the original &productname; DVD-ROMs and a flash disk. You do not need "
"to set up an installation server nor the network environment."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17305
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Create the control file and name it <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> . Copy "
"the file <filename>autoinst.xml</filename> to the flash disk."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17312
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Combining the <command>linuxrc</command> <filename>info</filename> File with "
"the &ay; Control File"
msgstr "&ay; 制御ファイルと <command>linuxrc</command> <filename>info</filename> ファイルの組み合わせ"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17313
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you choose to pass information to <command>linuxrc</command> using the "
"<filename>info</filename> file, it is possible to integrate the keywords in "
"the XML control file. In this case the file needs to be accessible to "
"<command>linuxrc</command> and must be named <filename>info</filename> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17320
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <command>linuxrc</command> program will look for the string "
"<literal>start_linuxrc_conf</literal> in the &ay; control file, which "
"represents the beginning of the embedded <command>linuxrc</command> control "
"file. If the string is found, <command>linuxrc</command> will parse the "
"content starting from that string and will finish when the string "
"<literal>end_linuxrc_conf</literal> is found. The options are stored in the "
"control file in the following way:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17330
#, no-c-format
msgid "<command>linuxrc</command> Options in the &ay; Control File"
msgstr "&ay; 制御ファイル内での <command>linuxrc</command> オプション"

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17331
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"....\n"
"  &lt;install&gt;\n"
"....\n"
"    &lt;init&gt;\n"
"      &lt;info_file&gt;\n"
"&lt;![CDATA[\n"
"#\n"
"# Do not remove the following line:\n"
"# start_linuxrc_conf\n"
"#\n"
"install: nfs://192.168.1.1/CDs/full-i386\n"
"textmode: 1\n"
"autoyast: file:///info\n"
"\n"
"# end_linuxrc_conf\n"
"# Do not remove the above comment\n"
"#\n"
"]]&gt;\n"
"\n"
"      &lt;/info_file&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/init&gt;\n"
"......\n"
"  &lt;/install&gt;\n"
"....\n"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Note that the <literal>autoyast</literal> keyword must point to the same "
"file. If it is on a flash disk, then the option <literal>usb:///</literal> "
"needs to be used. If the <filename>info</filename> file is stored in the "
"initial RAM disk, the <literal>file://</literal> option needs to be used."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17367
#, no-c-format
msgid "System Configuration"
msgstr "システム設定"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17369
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The system configuration during auto-installation is the most important part "
"of the whole process. As you have seen in the previous chapters, almost "
"anything can be configured automatically on the target system. In addition "
"to the pre-defined directives, you can always use post-scripts to change "
"other things in the system. Additionally you can change any system "
"variables, and if required, copy complete configuration files into the "
"target system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17380
#, no-c-format
msgid "Post-Install and System Configuration"
msgstr "インストール後およびシステムの設定"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17381
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The post-installation and system configuration are initiated directly after "
"the last package is installed on the target system and continue after the "
"system has booted for the first time."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Before the system is booted for the first time, &ay; writes all data "
"collected during installation and writes the boot loader in the specified "
"location. In addition to these regular tasks, &ay; executes the chroot-"
"scripts as specified in the control file. Note that these scripts are "
"executed while the system is not yet mounted."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17393
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a different kernel than the default is installed, a hard reboot will be "
"required. A hard reboot can also be forced during auto-installation, "
"independent of the installed kernel. Use the <literal>reboot</literal> "
"property of the <literal>general</literal> resource (see <xref linkend="
"\"CreateProfile.General\"/> )."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17403
#, no-c-format
msgid "System Customization"
msgstr "システムのカスタマイズ"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17404
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most of the system customization is done in the second stage of the "
"installation. If you require customization that cannot be done using &ay; "
"resources, use post-install scripts for further modifications."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17409
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can define an unlimited number of custom scripts in the control file, "
"either by editing the control file or by using the configuration system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17418
#, no-c-format
msgid "Running &ay; in an Installed System"
msgstr "インストール済みのシステム内での &ay; の実行"

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17419
#, no-c-format
msgid "In some cases it is useful to run &ay; in a running system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17422
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the following example, an additional software package ( <literal>foo</"
"literal> ) is going to be installed. To run this software, a user needs to "
"be added and an NTP client needs to be configured."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The respective &ay; profile needs to include a section for the package "
"installation ( <xref linkend=\"Software.Selections.stage2_packs\"/> ), a "
"user ( <xref linkend=\"Configuration.Security.users\"/> ) section and an NTP-"
"client ( <xref linkend=\"Configuration.Network.Ntp\"/> ) section:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: ay_bigfile.xml:17433
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&lt;?xml version=\"1.0\"?&gt;\n"
"&lt;!DOCTYPE profile&gt;\n"
"&lt;profile xmlns=\"http://www.suse.com/1.0/yast2ns\" xmlns:config=\"http://"
"www.suse.com/1.0/configns\"&gt;\n"
"  &lt;ntp-client&gt;\n"
"    &lt;peers config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;peer&gt;\n"
"        &lt;address&gt;us.pool.ntp.org&lt;/address&gt;\n"
"        &lt;comment/&gt;\n"
"        &lt;options&gt; iburst&lt;/options&gt;\n"
"        &lt;type&gt;server&lt;/type&gt;\n"
"      &lt;/peer&gt;\n"
"    &lt;/peers&gt;\n"
"    &lt;start_at_boot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;true&lt;/start_at_boot&gt;\n"
"    &lt;start_in_chroot config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/"
"start_in_chroot&gt;\n"
"    &lt;sync_interval config:type=\"integer\"&gt;5&lt;/sync_interval&gt;\n"
"    &lt;synchronize_time config:type=\"boolean\"&gt;false&lt;/"
"synchronize_time&gt;\n"
"  &lt;/ntp-client&gt;\n"
"  &lt;software&gt;\n"
"    &lt;post-packages config:type=\"list\"&gt;\n"
"      &lt;package&gt;ntp&lt;/package&gt;\n"
"      &lt;package&gt;yast2-ntp-client&lt;/package&gt;\n"
